  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. The FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors have been assessed; one factor (Test conditions) falls below the required level due to a single test condition. This model has been applied in clinical research evaluating spinal implant fatigue margins, and the simulation outputs have informed pre-market submissions. The assessment team considers the overall credibility sufficient for the intended regulatory submission context.",
