      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented V&V procedures. Software version control and regression testing records were reviewed and found compliant with institutional QMS requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Patch tests and benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10 were executed against analytical solutions. Maximum relative error in benchmark cases was below 0.5%, confirming correct implementation of the linear static solver."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed. The Richardson extrapolation-based Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for peak von Mises stress at the screw-rod junction was 1.8%, satisfying the required threshold of less than 5%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
