      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Residual convergence criteria were set to 1e-6 for all degrees of freedom. Solver logs confirmed convergence within tolerance for all 11 model instances. No spurious energy modes were detected."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Model setup was independently reviewed by a second analyst. Boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions were verified against the documented simulation plan. No discrepancies were identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic continuum mechanics is well-established for metallic spinal implants under quasi-static loading within the elastic regime. The selected model form is consistent with prior FDA guidance and published literature for ASTM F1717 simulation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (Ti-6Al-4V ELI, UHMWPE block) were sourced from ASTM-certified coupon testing and peer-reviewed literature. Geometric inputs were derived from certified CMM measurements of production implants. Sensitivity analysis confirmed that ±10% variation in elastic modulus produced less than 3% change in predicted stiffness."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 production-representative constructs were tested across two independent laboratories. Samples were drawn from the same manufacturing lot and inspected for dimensional conformance prior to testing, ensuring representativeness of the modeled geometry."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single load level (1400 N compression with 10 Nm bending moment) per the ASTM F1717 protocol. The absence of multiple load conditions limits the ability to validate model linearity assumptions across the full operating range. This factor falls below the required level and is documented as an identified gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Simulation boundary conditions were mapped directly from measured experimental fixture geometry and applied load magnitudes. Contact interface friction coefficients were calibrated to match experimentally observed construct stiffness within 4%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Predicted construct stiffness and yield load were compared against experimental measurements using the U95 metric per ASME V&V 10. Simulation predictions fell within the experimental uncertainty band for 10 of 11 specimens. The single outlier was attributed to a documented specimen assembly anomaly."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and peak stress at the screw-rod interface are the primary quantities of interest for fatigue life prediction and regulatory submission. These quantities are directly measurable in the ASTM F1717 test and are the outputs reported in the FEA model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity replicates the ASTM F1717 standardized test configuration, which is the accepted regulatory benchmark for pedicle screw construct performance. The validation domain is therefore directly relevant to the submission context in which this model has been applied in clinical research and pre-market evaluation."
    }
